  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      Hypokalemia is very common in heart failure patients. Deleterious effects have been report on
      the cardiovascular system. Most of the clinical data concerning this ionic trouble are based
      on post-hoc study and some findings seemed disjointed.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
  <detailed_description>
    <textblock>
      This study tried to describe hypokalemia impact during hospital stay in hospitalized patients
      with heart failure and particularly on mortality and re-hospitalization.
    </textblock>
  </detailed_description>
